## Dead Ends
- OTel-based design (mirror Python): rejected. ADK-JS emits OTel spans via
  the GLOBAL tracer; capturing them requires weave to register the global
  TracerProvider + ContextManager, which would break any user OTel setup
  registered later (setGlobalTracerProvider refuses second registration).
  Also SDK 2.x removed addSpanProcessor so we can't attach to an existing
  user provider. Python can patch ADK's tracing functions in-place;
  JS/ESM immutable bindings + relative internal imports make that impossible.
- Parenting @google/genai generateContent calls under ADK calls (the
  openai-agents approach via getCallStackFromOpenAIAgents): requires ambient
  correlation at generateContent time. Without a registered OTel
  ContextManager, ADK's context propagation is a no-op and NonRecording
  spans share the INVALID (all-zero) span id, so OTel-spanId correlation
  only works when a real global provider exists. Module-global "current
  model call" correlation breaks under ParallelAgent. Chose exclusion of
  ADK-internal genai clients instead (single source of truth = plugin).

## Hints for Future Agents
- ADK 1.2.0 NEVER dispatches plugin beforeAgentCallback/afterAgentCallback:
  PluginManager.runBefore/AfterAgentCallback exist but have ZERO call sites
  (handleBeforeAgentCallback only runs agent-level callbacks). WeaveAdkPlugin
  therefore synthesizes invoke_agent calls lazily from callbackContext
  .agentName + the agent tree captured at beforeRun (findAgent/parentAgent
  walk). Both agent callbacks ARE implemented in the plugin so timing
  becomes exact if ADK ever wires them; afterAgentCallback also deletes the
  map entry so LoopAgent iterations would get fresh calls.
- PluginManager RETHROWS plugin callback errors into the user's run — every
  WeaveAdkPlugin callback body is wrapped in guard() (warnOnce + swallow).
  Never let a logging bug break the host app.
- afterToolCallback fires even after onToolErrorCallback handled the same
  tool call (with result=null); endToolCall tolerates the missing map entry.
- afterModelCallback fires once per streamed response; partial=true chunks
  are skipped, the final aggregated response (partial falsy) closes the call.
- ADK-internal GoogleGenAI clients carry x-goog-api-client header containing
  'google-adk/<version>' (BaseLlm.trackingHeaders); googleGenAI.ts's
  constructor Proxy now skips wrapping those (isAdkInternalClientOptions).
  If ADK ever changes that header the exclusion silently stops and you'd
  see duplicate usage (call_llm + child generateContent root traces).
- CJS hook subPath for @google/adk is dist/cjs/index.js (package is
  type:module with a require condition). InMemoryRunner extends Runner, so
  patching Runner.prototype.runAsync/runEphemeral covers subclasses; the
  patch self-registers a process-wide shared plugin instance (globalSingleton
  '_weave_adk_instrumentation') guarded by pluginManager.getPlugin('weave').
- If a run aborts (exception propagates out of runAsync), afterRunCallback
  never fires; a process.once('beforeExit') hook force-closes dangling calls
  with status 'interrupted'. The client's batch timer keeps the loop alive
  long enough to flush.
- Mandatory ordering: weave must be imported BEFORE @google/adk in CJS hosts;
  ESM hosts need node --import=weave/instrument.
- E2E scratch lives at /tmp/weave-adk-e2e (main.js CJS, main.mjs ESM) and
  verifies against prod by reading calls back; rerun real Gemini with
  USE_REAL_GEMINI=true GOOGLE_GENAI_USE_VERTEXAI=true GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT=
  wandb-qa GOOGLE_CLOUD_LOCATION=us-central1 after gcloud auth
  application-default login, or GOOGLE_API_KEY + USE_REAL_GEMINI=true.

